# Tharun AI Portfolio — Cursor Rules

## Environment
- Python version: 3.13.6 (strictly — never suggest Python 3.14, no prebuilt wheels)
- Node version: use whatever Next.js 14 installed
- Virtual environment: backend/venv — always activate before running Python commands
- Windows terminal commands: use backslash paths and .\venv\Scripts\activate

## Project Identity
This is a production-grade agentic voice portfolio for Venkata Tharun Parsa.
Every decision prioritizes: reliability > intelligence > speed > cost.

## Core Rules — Never Violate
1. Every agent must have error handling and a fallback response
2. No LLM call happens without passing through verification_agent first
3. RAG responses must include similarity score checks — reject if score < 0.75
4. Never expose API keys — always use config.py and environment variables
5. Every function must have a docstring explaining what it does
6. All external API calls must be wrapped in try/except with fallback
7. LangGraph state must be typed using TypedDict
8. FastAPI endpoints must have proper response models and status codes
9. Never import unused libraries
10. Always log agent decisions using LangSmith tracing

## Architecture Rules
- verification_agent.py → rule-based only, zero LLM calls, runs first always
- intent_classifier.py → Groq LLaMA only (fast + cheap)
- rag_agent.py → Gemini Flash + Supabase pgvector
- tts.py → ElevenLabs for responses under 200 chars, Web Speech API for longer
- cache.py → check Redis before any LLM call
- All agents return consistent AgentResponse TypedDict

## Code Style
- Python: PEP8, type hints everywhere, docstrings on every function
- JavaScript: functional components only, no class components
- TailwindCSS: use CSS variables for theming, no inline styles
- Always handle loading states and error states in frontend components

## Guardrails — Always Enforce
- Agent must never discuss: personal relationships, salary, politics, religion, legal advice, medical advice
- Agent must never hallucinate — if RAG score < 0.75, respond with uncertainty message
- Agent must never answer out of scope questions about Tharun
- All responses must be grounded in knowledge base only

## File Naming
- Python files: snake_case
- React components: PascalCase
- Config files: lowercase with dots

## Deployment Targets
- Backend: Render.com (Python FastAPI)
- Frontend: Vercel (Next.js)
- Never hardcode URLs — use environment variables for all endpoints
